section.section:
"Licensing information" means a statement of:
each license held by the defendant on the date of sentencing;
the full name of the licensee as it appears on the license and, if different, as it appears in the court's docket;
the birth date of the licensee; and
the name of each licensing authority by whom the defendant is licensed.

If the individual holds a license, at sentencing, the court shall make a prima facie finding of fact as to whether a relationship exists between the conviction and the license including:
a determination of the individual's ability to perform the tasks authorized by the license;
a finding of whether the public will be protected if the individual continues to perform the tasks authorized by the license;
a finding of whether the nature and circumstances of the drug crime merit referral to the licensing authority; and
a finding of any other facts that the court considers relevant.
